contentrichtext.text: {{unsourced|date=March 2009}} '''Jorge Toriello Garrido''' (died 1998) was one of the three leaders of the first government that ruled [[Guatemala]] from 20 October 1944 to 15 March 1945 as part of the [[October Revolution]]. Toriello Garrido, a civilian, led the government along with [[Jacobo Arbenz Guzmán|Captain Jacobo Arbenz Guzmán]] and [[Francisco Javier Arana|Major Francisco Javier Arana]] after overthrowing the military regime of [[Juan Federico Ponce Vaides]], who had temporarily taken over from ousted dictator [[Jorge Ubico]]. {{GuatemalaPres}} {{Persondata <!-- Metadata: see [[Wikipedia:Persondata]]. --> | NAME = Toriello Garrido, Jorge | ALTERNATIVE NAMES = | SHORT DESCRIPTION = President of Guatemala | DATE OF BIRTH = | PLACE OF BIRTH = | DATE OF DEATH = 1998 | PLACE OF DEATH = }} {{DEFAULTSORT:Toriello Garrido, Jorge}} [[Category:Year of birth missing]] [[Category:1998 deaths]] [[Category:Presidents of Guatemala]] {{Guatemala-politician-stub}} {{NorthAm-mil-bio-stub}}
